The paper focuses on detecting fake social engagement activities on YouTube, which falls under the category of social media analysis. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with spam detection, which falls under the category of cybersecurity, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) another likely sub-category. The paper uses graph analysis and machine learning techniques, which are common in information retrieval, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category. The paper also deals with large-scale data processing, which falls under the category of data science, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with social network analysis, which falls under the category of social computing, making cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) a possible sub-category.
